comments: Curry (DAL) makes marginal contact with Booker (PHX) at the end of his drive.
Hardaway Jr. (DAL) places and releases a marginal hand to Booker's (PHX) body during the shot attempt near the basket.
Johnson (PHX) is moving alongside Doncic's (DAL) path and maintains a legal guarding position as he defends the drive to the basket.
Doncic (DAL) extends his arm as he releases from the contact with Johnson (PHX).
Booker (PHX) moves laterally into Curry's (PHX) path and affects his SQBR.
Porzingis (DAL) avoids making contact with Bridges (PHX) as he sets the screen.
Bridges (PHX) makes marginal contact with Doncic (DAL) at the start of his drive and he is able to move through it and stay on his direct path toward the basket.
Bridges (PHX) legally contests Doncic's (DAL) driving shot attempt.
Rubio (PHX) is already in Porzingis' (DAL) path when contact occurs and he does not deliver contact.

Replay review of the foul called on Porzingis (DAL) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed successful. During review, referees determined that it was Finney-Smith (DAL) and not Porzingis who fouled Rubio (PHX).
Porzingis (DAL) is already in Rubio's (PHX) path when contact occurs and he does not deliver contact.
Porzingis (DAL) is already in Bridges' (PHX) path when contact occurs and he does not deliver contact.
Porzingis (DAL) is already in Bridges' (PHX) path and Porzingis extends his arms as he releases from the contact.
Carter (PHX) and Hardaway Jr. (DAL) briefly engage and disengage during the inbound.
Doncic (DAL) receives the pass and proceeds to take three steps prior to starting his dribble.
Doncic (DAL) extends his arm as he releases from the contact with Bridges (PHX).
Bridges (PHX) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Doncic's (DAL) drive to the basket.
Ayton (PHX) legally contests Porzingis' (DAL) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Porzingis (DAL) gives Carter (PHX) room to avoid the contact.
Johnson (PHX) and Finney-Smith (DAL) engage and separate during the rebound.
Carter (PHX) legally contests Hardaway Jr.'s (DAL) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
